text.tspan: I'm a hacker commited to the values of the software freedom movement.
Skills: IT training & education, libre software development and advocacy, copyright research,
pcb design, digital electronics, reverse engineering, device driver development, digital fabrication,
open standards, public speaking, technical writing, 3d modelling, graphic design.

Metamquina is a 3D printing business focused on popularizing rapid prototyping machines in Brazil.
We're fully commited to software freedom and open hardware designs.
* Company's lead role in R&D
* Hardware design and software/firmware development for an open hardware 3D printer (Metamquina 2)
* Regular contributions to upstream free software projects such as OpenSCAD and Repetier-Firmware.
* Management of the Metamquina 2 production line.

* Lecturer in several educational workshops covering topics such as 3D modelling, 3D printers maintainence and operation, free software development tools, hacker ethics and open innovation. Workshops also included guided assembly and educational exploration of DIY hardware kits,
reverse engineering techniques and learning by tinkering in general.
* Tutorship at extra-curricular STEM classes at the Saint Paul's british school in So Paulo, Brazil.

text.tspan: Libre Software development at FontBakery, Metapolator and other typography-related projects

flowRoot.flowPara: https://github.com/googlefonts/fontbakery/
Development of FontBakery, a set of automated quality assurance checks for a large set
of font files prior to submission to Google Web Fonts.
http://metapolator.com/
Software development for the Metapolator project, a web application that helps
type designers working on parametric type design.
* Import and Export routines supporting the Zipped UFO file format.
* OpenType.js integration to also handle the OTF file format.
